        "title": "Core Concepts of Thai Cuisine",
        "content": "Thai cuisine is celebrated for its balance of flavors, including:\n- **Sweet**: Often derived from palm sugar or fruits.\n- **Sour**: Commonly from lime juice or tamarind.\n- **Salty**: Typically from fish sauce or soy sauce."
      },
      {
        "title": "Flavor Balance in Dishes",
        "content": "Understanding the balance of flavors is crucial:\n- **Sweetness** often complements sourness.\n- **Sourness** balances the richness of salty components.\n- Each dish aims for harmony among these tastes."
      },
      {
        "title": "The Importance of Ingredients",
        "content": "The secret to authentic Thai cooking lies in:\n- Using fresh, high-quality ingredients.\n- Incorporating traditional staples like fish sauce and palm sugar.\n- Understanding how each ingredient contributes to the overall flavor profile."
      }
    ]
  }
